{
  "_readme": "Oryx 16-bit Fantasy sprite floor-tile map for a dungeon generator. Each 'style' is one horizontal band of the top-left wall/floor block; the wall material of that band defines its color theme. For each style we list the COLOR-MATCHED floor tiles (sheet columns 3-6). HOW TO USE: for a room of a given style, pick one tile whose role=='base' as the main fill (weight it heavily / flood most of the floor), then optionally sprinkle role=='accent' tiles sparsely (cracks, embers, emblems, checkerboard, transition edges) for variation. A style may have several valid bases (pick one, or mix a couple of similar-tone bases) and may have zero accents. Never use an 'accent' as the dominant fill. Tiles marked GLOW (style 9 col6, style 14 col5/col6) are vivid emissive tiles \u2014 treat as rare hero accents. Style 17 (Homestead Pickets) is a fence PROP row, not a real dungeon wall; its floors are generic dark filler.",
  "_schema": {
    "sheet_file": "oryx_16bit_fantasy_world_trans.png",
    "tile_size": 24,
    "coordinate_system": "pixel origin top-left; a tile's rect is [x, y, w, h] in pixels, ready to crop directly.",
    "column_layout": {
      "note": "Per style band the leftmost empty column is dropped, then columns are 0-indexed.",
      "col0": "solid wall face (NOT a floor)",
      "col1": "cracked wall face (NOT a floor)",
      "col2": "shattered wall face (NOT a floor)",
      "col3": "floor tile",
      "col4": "floor tile",
      "col5": "floor tile",
      "col6": "floor tile"
    },
    "style_fields": "id, name, aka(optional), material, wall_hex(theme color from wall face), floors[]",
    "floor_fields": "col, rect[x,y,w,h], role(base|accent), hex, hint",
    "quick_lists": "each style also has base_cols[] and accent_cols[] for fast selection"
  },
